
configuring the datasource...
   lb datasource

starting the mongodb database...
   mongodb -port 9334 -dbpath /home/gates/sandbox/git.checkout/grocery_list/extra/db

starting the mongo client
   mongo --port 9334

to switch to the grocery list database
   use grocery_list
   
to be the admin...
   use admin

to see the users...
   show users

allowed roles for a user...
   read,
   readAnyDatabase,
   readWrite,
   readWriteAnyDatabase,
   dbAdmin,
   dbAdminAnyDatabase,
   clusterAdmin,
   userAdmin,
   userAdminAnyDatabase
   
to add a user...
   db.createUser(
       {user: "gates",
        pwd: "blah",
	roles: ["readWrite", "dbAdmin"]})

   Hmm, addUser is DEPRECATED.  Supposed to use createUser
   
to remove a user...
   db.removeUser( {user: "gates"} )

adding stuff to the database...
   col = db.getCollection("items")
   col.insert({name: "bread", cost: "$3.99", aisle: "12"})
   